<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧊 M003 Extension 2 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> 3D Mob Heads (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner (Extension, after Week 3) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>Build a mob head in 3D. Every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>: x <strong>across</strong>, y <strong>up</strong>, z <strong>deeper</strong> (forward).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move, and the head moves too.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the code. Circle one word.</p>
<pre><code>place green block at (3, 5, 1)
place green block at (3, 5, 2)
place green block at (3, 5, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only z changes. Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<pre><code>place green block at (4, 5, 1)
place green block at (4, 6, 1)
place green block at (4, 7, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only y changes. Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>This eye should be one step <strong>deeper</strong>, at (4, 7, 2). The code below only has <strong>two</strong> numbers, so it lands on the front.</p>
<pre><code># broken
place black block at (4, 7)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fill the blank to fix it:</strong></p>
<pre><code>place black block at (4, 7, __)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which number fills the blank? Circle one:</strong> 2 · 1</p>
<p><strong>What was missing? Circle one:</strong> the z number · the color</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Look at the 🟢 creeper head in the world. Walk around it.</p>
<p><strong>Build a small solid head — a cube.</strong> Keep it easy:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Front face: fill green blocks from (3, 5, 1) up to (5, 7, 1) — a small square.</p>
<p>Add depth: build the same square again at z = 2, then z = 3.</p>
<p>Add 2 eyes on the front only: black block at (3, 7, 1) and black block at (5, 7, 1).</p>
<p>💡 Tip: the eyes only show on the <strong>front</strong>. The sides and back are plain green.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> — one take, no stopping (a phone is fine). Show these in order:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Say these out loud, filling in the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
<p>The most fun part was ______.</p>
<p>Something new I learned was ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
